Vietnam Approves Coal-Port Construction, Saigon Giai Phong Says

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-05-19T08:30:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/vietnam-approves-coal-port-construction-saigon-giai-phong-says.html
Vietnam ’s government approved plans
to build a coal trans-shipment port in the country’s south,
 Saigon Giai Phong  reported today.  The port, proposed by Vietnam National Coal-Mineral
Industries Group, will handle thermal coal for  power plants  in
the Mekong Delta, the newspaper said. Vinacomin, as the company
is known, will provide the capital for the project, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  